For the price we paid (CAD$194.48/night plus $20/day for parking) , we expected breakfast to be included but was told when we got there, breakfast was an extra CAD$16/person.	Usually would stay at Chez Swann hotel, but it gets expensive on the weekends (see my review on tripadvisor), so ended up staying here for the first time, because of reviews and price.	It came for ~ 140 CAD which for location and service was a great value.	Overall, it was an okay stay, but we would not stay there again because it is not good value for money.	We found a very good rate for this stay, and would certainly stay here again (if the price is right).